{
  "stem": "9168.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So there was only one place for me to go, and that was into the court reporting course for three months.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I went in every morning on the 400 Northwestern train at 7:00 AM, at this little, tiny town train station.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I got into Chicago at 8:30, and into Union station; walked two blocks to get a bus to go to Michigan Avenue, and then off the bus; and walked two blocks to Gregg College, which was on Michigan Avenue-- number six, Michigan Avenue.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And at that time, I was really interested in that court reporting course.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After three months, I was well into the course and gaining speed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And every night, I had to travel back out to Woodstock.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The exciting thing about those train trips was that in our little town of Woodstock also lived Chester Gould, who drew Dick Tracy.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we got on the same train every morning and the same train every night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he would let me sit with him while he pulled out his art frame, and would draw another frame for Dick Tracy.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At any rate, that made the trip a little bit easier-- less time for studying, because I was so interested in his art.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At-- however, after three months, my mother borrowed more money, and more money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I knew that this was a two year course.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I finished it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I managed to finish the course and pass the required 200 words per minute in shorthand-- Gregg shorthand-- reporting shorthand-- not secretarial shorthand, which is a very abbreviated system-- in 13 months.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have no idea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe I showed the ability to gain greater speed early on in the teaching of manual shorthand.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
